    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="384"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/1561</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chinese Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wei</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency, the Chinese
                    Ambassador, and has the honor to refer to the latter’s note of October 18,
                        1943,<note n="71" xml:id="d384fn71">Not printed.</note> regarding the
                    manufacture of certain memorial medals by the United States Mint.</p>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of the Treasury has now informed the Department that he has
                    instructed the Director of the Mint to make available facilities at one of the
                    United States Mints for the manufacture of these medals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-26">November 26,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
